@mvromer are you still seeing this? 

The reason you can see the port from other distributions is because they all share the same kernel. If you see the problem and you stop via `podman machine stop` and then you do `wsl --shutdown`, followed by `podman machine start` does the port work and start showing up?

What version of WSL are you running (you can access this via `wsl --version`)?

@n1hility Interesting bit about all WSL distros sharing the same kernel. I did not know that.

To answer your question, at the time I had to remove my podman machine and I believe I also reinstalled podman for good measure. I then reinit my podman machine and haven't had problems since.

If I do run into it again, I'll run the extra diagnostic steps above and report back here.

@tppalani based on your client version, there is a good chance you are affected by a problem fixed in 4.5 that shows up after creating a machine after F37 updates were incorporated (https://github.com/containers/podman/pull/17686)

If that’s the issue you would need to update your client to the latest 4.5.1 (although the fix was incorporated in 4.5.0), and then rebuild your machine with (`podman machine rm; podman machine init`).

A temporary workaround for this problem (if it is the one you are seeing) is to manually restore shadow utils on the machine instance: `podman machine stop` followed by `wsl -u root -d podman-machine-default rpm --restore shadow-utils`
